  "description": [
    "HURRICANE SWEEPS CITY OF GALVESTON REPORTS RECEIVED TODAY ARE ALARMING Since The First News That The Storm Had Driven Water Over The Sea Wall And The Streets Were Seven Feet Under Water All Wires Have Been Down And No Further Com munication Had With The Island The great Galveston storm of September 8 1OO which almost completely submerged hat city and destroyed millions of dollars worth of property and manv of human lives is yet fresh in the memory of het world as one of the greatest disasters of modern times and the prayers of all will go up for the safety of this great sea port of Texas The news received by The Times up to the hour of going to press gives the following account Houston July 21It is reported from Galveston severe damage was done there from water driven before a fifty mile wind blowing off o the gulf The water was carried over the sea wall and the western part of the city is under water A low barometer exists and all wires out of commission and the details are not yet known Washington July 21 The weather bureau has a report of a severe storm"
  ],
